    jSimPack
    A discrete event simulator
    simulator.framework
    Provides the core infrastructure for simulating the network and elevator.

    • Uses of FutureEvent in jSimPack

      Methods in jSimPack that return FutureEvent 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      FutureEvent FutureEventList.schedule(FutureEventListener event, SimTime timeInterval, java.lang.Object data)
      Schedules the specified event to happen in the future.
      FutureEvent FutureEventList.scheduleNonsimulationEvent(FutureEventListener event, SimTime timeInterval, java.lang.Object data)
      Works just like scheduleEvent, but puts the event into the system queue (which are executed first and do not affect the random permutation of other events).

      Modifier and Type Method and Description

      Cancel the event associated with label.
      void FutureEventList.cancelNonsimulationEvent(FutureEvent event)
      Works jsut like cancelEvent but for nonsimulation events.
      int FutureEvent.compareTo(FutureEvent e)
      Implementation of the Comparable interface - comparison is based on event time.
